ðŸ› ï¸ Task 2.2: Calculate the Costs After Optimization
ðŸ”§ Configuration Changes (After Optimization):
Component	Optimization Change
EC2 Instance	- Changed instance type from t2.small â†’ t2.micro
EBS Volume	- Reduced size from 40 GB â†’ 20 GB (removed old DB data)
RDS Instance	- Unchanged
________________________________________
ðŸ“Š Steps to Modify Estimate (After Optimization):
1.	Edit EC2 Entry:
o	Click Edit next to EC2
o	Change Instance type to t2.micro
o	Change EBS storage to 20 GB
o	Click Update
2.	Export Estimate:
o	Click Export > CSV
o	Save file to your system
